HEADWORD: Antiperiodic
<hw>An`ti*pe`ri*od"ic</hw>
<pr>(⟦acr⟧n`t⟦icr⟧*p⟦emac⟧`r⟦icr⟧*⟦ocr⟧d"⟦icr⟧k)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A remedy possessing the property of preventing
the return of periodic paroxysms, or exacerbations, of disease, as in
intermittent fevers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Antiperistaltic</ent>⟦br⟧
